00:47:16.834 --> 00:47:20.113
- He's kicking your ass and
talking shit at the same time.

759
00:47:20.182 --> 00:47:21.666
- Pot's right.
Let's do it.

760
00:47:21.735 --> 00:47:24.669
- Yeah. that's right. I do have
the boat you little bastard.

761
00:47:24.738 --> 00:47:28.328
Aces up.
- Oh!

762
00:47:28.397 --> 00:47:30.537
It's your bedtime.
- So did I.

763
00:47:30.606 --> 00:47:31.745
- Oh!

764
00:47:33.505 --> 00:47:36.439
- The same exact cards
last time.

765
00:47:40.616 --> 00:47:43.205
- If you're so sad. how about
I play you something happy?

766
00:47:46.415 --> 00:47:49.107
- No. I need to cry.

767
00:47:52.559 --> 00:47:54.941
But I'm incapable
of crying for myself.

768
00:47:55.010 --> 00:47:58.151
Walker. I need a song
to cry to.

769
00:48:01.637 --> 00:48:04.709
- This is about a man
who got killed that...

770
00:48:04.778 --> 00:48:05.883
wasn't quite ready to die.

771
00:48:07.850 --> 00:48:11.923
Guess as his soul
was floating up in the air

772
00:48:11.992 --> 00:48:15.754
he's looking down on all
the things he was gonna miss.

773
00:48:15.823 --> 00:48:17.722
Pretty sure he cried.

774
00:48:20.518 --> 00:48:22.485
- Yeah. that sounds
like a song for me.

775
00:48:39.778 --> 00:48:43.403
♪ The other day I found
myself up on the corner ♪

776
00:48:43.472 --> 00:48:47.510
♪ I thought I run into
a friend of mine ♪

777
00:48:47.579 --> 00:48:50.893
♪ Ended up he was
just a stranger ♪

778
00:48:50.962 --> 00:48:53.551
♪ Said hello
and he passed me by ♪

779
00:49:01.248 --> 00:49:04.665
♪ But then he turned
and put a gun to my head ♪

780
00:49:04.734 --> 00:49:08.704
♪ He said my friend.
I'm gonna rob you blind ♪

781
00:49:08.773 --> 00:49:11.741
♪ I said you must be
down on your luck ♪

782
00:49:11.810 --> 00:49:15.124
♪ I'm outta money
and I'm all out of time ♪

783
00:49:30.070 --> 00:49:33.418
♪ He pulled the trigger
and I fell to my knees ♪

784
00:49:33.487 --> 00:49:35.869
♪ My spirit left
and then my body went cold ♪

785
00:49:37.319 --> 00:49:40.391
♪ I'm looking down upon
the lights of the city ♪

786
00:49:40.460 --> 00:49:43.981
♪ I feel alive
but I'm dead and gone ♪

787
00:49:57.063 --> 00:49:59.997
♪ Ain't no more favors
from someone I don't know ♪

788
00:50:00.066 --> 00:50:02.206
♪ 'Cause there ain't
nobody hear me ♪

789
00:50:02.275 --> 00:50:04.104
♪ Nobody's around ♪

790
00:50:06.072 --> 00:50:09.972
♪ Hallelujah ♪

791
00:50:10.041 --> 00:50:11.525
♪ He's dead and gone ♪

792
00:50:13.803 --> 00:50:16.565
♪ Hallelujah ♪

793
00:50:24.538 --> 00:50:28.094
- Do I have to go up
on the hill too?

794
00:50:28.163 --> 00:50:29.371
- Some day.

795
00:50:29.440 --> 00:50:31.649
- When?

796
00:50:31.718 --> 00:50:32.719
- When your heart tells you to.

797
00:50:35.411 --> 00:50:36.964
- Right here. Tate.

798
00:51:06.787 --> 00:51:07.892
- Gotta be honest.

799
00:51:10.481 --> 00:51:12.483
Not sure I believe
in all this.

800
00:51:12.552 --> 00:51:14.140
- It sure believes in you.

801
00:51:15.969 --> 00:51:17.522
Hey...

802
00:51:17.591 --> 00:51:19.662
Wherever something
good's trying to happen

803
00:51:19.731 --> 00:51:21.940
something bad is trying
to stop it.

804
00:51:22.009 --> 00:51:24.978
Your only safe place
is inside your prayer ties.

805
00:51:26.152 --> 00:51:27.774
Your only protection
is the pipe.

806
00:51:31.433 --> 00:51:34.160
Everything else
around you could be evil.

807
00:51:35.747 --> 00:51:40.476
Beware the coyote. he is the
trickster and cannot be trusted.

808
00:51:42.133 --> 00:51:43.169
- How long is Hanbleceya?

809
00:51:44.377 --> 00:51:46.068
- Four days
and four nights.

810
00:51:46.137 --> 00:51:48.691
No food.
No water.

811
00:51:50.348 --> 00:51:51.591
- No water?

812
00:51:51.660 --> 00:51:53.386
- None.

813
00:51:53.455 --> 00:51:54.870
- I'll die.

814
00:51:54.939 --> 00:51:56.975
- You must stand
on the cliff of death

815
00:51:57.044 --> 00:52:00.669
to understand
your purpose in life.

816
00:52:00.738 --> 00:52:02.740
It's the only place
where you can see it.

817
00:52:13.682 --> 00:52:15.097
She's a good woman.

818
00:52:17.858 --> 00:52:19.032
- Better than I deserve.

819
00:52:20.067 --> 00:52:22.449
- God doesn't work like that.

820
00:52:22.518 --> 00:52:25.521
He would never let her love
someone who didn't deserve her.

821
00:53:12.844 --> 00:53:14.191
- I feel kinda silly.

822
00:53:15.468 --> 00:53:17.366
- Listen to Mo.

823
00:53:17.435 --> 00:53:19.610
Do what he says
exactly as he says it.

824
00:53:22.440 --> 00:53:23.786
I love you.

825
00:53:31.277 --> 00:53:32.623
- See you in a few days.

826
00:54:50.563 --> 00:54:53.428
Use the sage to keep
bad spirits off.

827
00:54:53.497 --> 00:54:56.293
Use the sweet grass to call
your spirit helpers in.

828
00:54:57.570 --> 00:55:00.193
Smoke the pipe when you pray.
Understand?

829
00:55:03.196 --> 00:55:06.372
- You'll be surprised
how quickly you'll replay

830
00:55:06.441 --> 00:55:09.306
all your moments
in life in your mind.

831
00:55:09.375 --> 00:55:11.860
And then what?

832
00:55:11.929 --> 00:55:16.140
When you are without memories.
without regrets to ponder.

833
00:55:16.209 --> 00:55:20.938
without fantasies
to embrace or to reject.

834
00:55:21.007 --> 00:55:23.837
what will you think of then?

835
00:55:23.906 --> 00:55:26.737
What will come to you depends

836
00:55:26.806 --> 00:55:30.568
on how hard you pray
and how much you suffer.

837
00:55:32.432 --> 00:55:33.847
Close him in. Mo.

838
00:55:50.312 --> 00:55:51.865
- How will you know
when I'm done?

839
00:55:53.142 --> 00:55:54.765
- How will you know. Kayce?

840
00:55:57.319 --> 00:55:58.562
That is the question.
